Colombia Offers to Buy Back May 2014 Bonds at 5.5% Yield

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-09-20T13:56:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/colombia-offers-to-buy-back-may-2014-bonds-at-5-5-yield-1-.html
Colombia  offered to buy back peso
debt due in May 2014 at a yield of 5.5 percent in an  exchange 
that seeks to extend maturities and issue a new 7.5 percent bond
due August 2026.  The  Finance Ministry  also will buy back as much as 12.3
trillion pesos ($6.6 billion) of its fixed-rate securities due
April 2012 and August 2012 at a yield of 4.8 percent, April 2013
at 5.1 percent and November 2013 at 5.4 percent, it said in a
statement today. Colombia will offer in return peso debt due
October 2015, October 2018 and August 2026.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  